<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head') %>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/cursor') %>
  <%- include('partials/nav') %>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="story-hero">
    <div class="story-hero-img-wrap">
      <img src="/images/al-banus.jpg" alt="Two Hearts — Shiny List Award" class="story-hero-img" style="object-position: center 10%;">
      <div class="story-hero-overlay"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="story-hero-content reveal">
      <span class="story-hero-category">Films</span>
      <h1 class="story-hero-title">Alasdair Braxton's 'Two Hearts' Secures Shiny List Award</h1>
      <span class="story-hero-date">March 1, 2026</span>
      <img src="/images/shiny-list-logo.png" alt="Shiny List" class="shiny-hero-logo">
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Article -->
  <section class="story-body">
    <div class="story-body-inner reveal">
      <p>Braxton Studios is thrilled to announce that Alasdair Braxton's short film, Two Hearts, has been officially recognised on the prestigious <a href="https://www.shinyawards.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="story-link">Shiny List</a>. This award celebrates emerging directorial talent and high-caliber visual storytelling, marking a significant achievement for both Alasdair and the studio. The recognition from Shiny List underscores our commitment to pushing the boundaries of digital cinema and narrative music films.</p>

      <p>The project draws its profound emotional core from Dermot Kennedy's I've Told the Trees Everything EP. Taking inspiration from the raw, lyrical themes of Kennedy's work, Two Hearts explores the complexities of love, memory, and the "beautiful feeling" of unrequited emotion. By translating these auditory landscapes into a visual medium, the film captures the haunting atmosphere of the original music while carving out its own unique cinematic identity.</p>

      <div class="story-inline-img">
        <img src="/images/kenmore-6-2.jpg" alt="Alasdair Braxton on location">
      </div>

      <p>Visually, the film navigates contrasting settings, such as the isolation of a winter station or the shared silence of a darkened theatre, to mirror the internal journey of its characters. The narrative follows a story of brief goodbyes and the lingering weight of things "you never leave behind." Through careful pacing and evocative imagery, Alasdair explores whether love can truly outweigh pain, creating a visceral experience that resonates with fans of the EP and independent film enthusiasts alike.</p>

      <p>This award-winning production serves as a testament to Braxton Studios' mission of making high-tier production effortless and impactful. By bridging the gap between musical inspiration and elite cinematography, Two Hearts demonstrates our ability to tell stories that are as strategically sound as they are artistically ambitious. We look forward to building on this momentum as we continue to develop innovative content for a global audience.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Watch -->
  <section class="story-video">
    <div class="story-video-inner reveal">
      <h2 class="story-video-heading">Watch Two Hearts</h2>
      <div class="story-video-embed">
        <iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/c8JALjk1DBE" title="Two Hearts — Alasdair Braxton" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('partials/signup') %>
  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
  <%- include('partials/scripts') %>
</body>
</html>
